      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">The Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) refers to the application of
                instrumentation and connected sensors and other devices to machinery and vehicles in
                the transport, energy, and other critical infrastructure sectors. In the energy
                sector, distributed energy resources (DERs) such as solar photovoltaics including
                sensors, data transfer and communications systems, instruments, and other
                commercially available devices that are networked together. DERs introduce
                information exchanges between a utility's distribution control system and the DERs
                to manage the flow of energy in the distribution grid.</abstract>
